%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: a183a5e5a25be724eb5376f2fe7a13fc, type: 3}
  m_Name: VideoInstruction_SO
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::VideoInstructionScriptableObjectScript
  videoInstructionList:
  - id: 0
    title: Buy Units From The Shop
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 8ae93fbe0c6d4fc4c8ea250675288d2b, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Click the Shop button to open the Shop. The button shows your current
      coin balance and updates as you earn or spend coins. Click a Unit Card to buy
      & add it to your inventory. You can also spend coins to refresh the available
      Unit Cards in the Shop.
  - id: 1
    title: Elemental Counters
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 0a943143f85111c4da24faf8315a379a, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: When deploying units, pay attention to elemental counters. Each
      element has a weakness & exploiting that with a counter element will let you
      to deal extra damage & break enemy shields faster.
  - id: 2
    title: Discard Unit Cards from Inventory
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: ad9fa1e148250084f9993a5248105eaf, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Drag and drop unwanted Unit cards from your inventory into the Discard
      panel to sell them back and recover some of the coins you spent
  - id: 3
    title: Valid & Invalid Tiles for deployment
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 51e09c0fce0170248b05ae5183e8ab47, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Units can only be placed on valid tiles within the deployment zone.
      Valid tiles are highlighted in green, while invalid tiles are highlighted in
      red. If you place a unit on an invalid tile, it will return to your inventory
      or its previous valid position.
  - id: 4
    title: Deployment Limit
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: bc4764205f4e04f49a9413866a7aca19, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: The bottom-right corner shows your Player Level, XP progress, and
      Unit Deployment Limit. As your level increases, you can deploy more units.
      You cannot place more units than your current deployment limit.
  - id: 5
    title: Increase Player Level
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 3056912d34d534e4cbe3c2b860ca5dda, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Click the Buy XP button to spend coins and gain XP. Each level requires
      more XP than the last. You start the first round with a set amount of coins.
      At the end of each round, you earn more coins whether you win, lose, or draw.
  - id: 6
    title: Increase Deployment Limit
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: cb0e906cfdbce1243a869d00b3c1b45a, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: As you level up, you'll unlock a higher unit deployment limit.
  - id: 7
    title: Discard Units from Field
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: 846befe1eaaffcf4198ef633fc79155c, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Drag and drop a unit directly from the field to the Discard panel
      to sell it and receive a coin refund.
  - id: 8
    title: Move Units to Inventory From Field
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: ea07f19e5e3aa5045a77adde517b5197, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Drag and drop a deployed unit from the field back into your inventory.
  - id: 9
    title: 'Unit Faction & Type Buffs '
    videoClip: {fileID: 32900000, guid: b735292893359764ba0805212f82abc5, type: 3}
    videoThumbnail: {fileID: 0}
    instruction: Deployed units receive stat buffs based on your field lineup. These
      buffs depend on the number of units from the same faction or type. Building
      the right combinations with the deployed units can increase damage, improve
      shields, enhance healing, and strengthen your team in a battle.
